/**
 * Returns an instant that is the result of subtracting components of [DateTimePeriod] from this instant. The components
 * are subtracted in the order from the largest units to the smallest, i.e. from years to nanoseconds.
 *
 * This function requires a [timeZone] parameter because calendar components like years, months, and days
 * do not have fixed lengths in absolute time due to variations like leap years and daylight saving time transitions.
 *
 * When performing this calculation, the function:
 * 1. Converts this instant to a local date-time in the specified time zone
 * 2. Subtracts the period's components from that local date-time 
 * 3. Converts the result back to an instant
 *
